args:
When village livestock are drained of all their
blood, Vania is eager to prove her innocence.
She slays the fiend responsible in front of the
villagers, but in a cruel irony, her overwhelming
vampiric power causes them to fear her.
All right, time for another day of fun and\ngames!
Ooh, hey there! What do you wanna play\ntoday? More hide-and-seek? Tag?!
Oh... Vania. I, um...\nSorry, I can't play today.
My... My mom won't let me.
Mine said I couldn't play with you anymore\neither, Vania...
I'm real sorry, but...\nUm, we've gotta go.
What?! Hey, wait! Don't leave! Guys?!
This extends beyond just the children.\nThe entire village seems to be avoiding us.
No... What happened, you guys?\nWhat changed?
Pretty sure I know. I hear cows 'n pigs\nhave been turnin' up dead in the village.
What does that have to do with Vania?
The manner in which the livestock died...\nThey'd been drained of all their blood.
So they think SHE did it?!
No way! I would never ever! I wouldn't\neven WANT to drink the blood of cows\nor pigs. That's gross!
Well, it don't sound like the villagers\nare lookin' to accuse you just yet...
Just, this only started happenin' since you\nturned up around here. Plus, you bein' a\nvampire an' all... They're a little leery.
And so, in their disquiet, they have chosen\nto treat my liege as a criminal, despite a\ntotal lack of evidence.
You humans are an irredeemable lot.
That's it—whoever did this is getting a\npiece of my mind!
Huh? Wait... You're not plannin' on trying\nto track down the perp yourself, are ya?
Well, obviously! Now c'mon, mister.\nWe're heading out!
Obviously! As my bloodkin, you have\nto help me. Those are the rules.
Vania, he's TOLD you he's not hitching\nhis caboose to your vampy train.
I'll wear him down eventually, so I don't\nsee any reason not to start his on-the-job\ntraining now.
Fine. The whole bloodkin issue aside,\nI'll help you look for the culprit.
I am. The victims may only be livestock for\nnow, but I don't fancy letting whoever it is\ngo around draining blood unchecked.
We'll root out the cause, and if it poses\na threat, I'll put an end to it myself.
That's enough dawdling, bloodkin. Let's go!
According to the villagers I spoke with,\nthe incidents all happened at night.
If we hide here and wait, we may be able\nto catch the culprit in the act.
I'm sleepy... If they haven't come by now,\nthey're not coming today.
That's quite possible... Perhaps rushing\ninto a stakeout was optimistic. We'll have\nto think of another way of—
What? Look closer, jeez. It's right there!
Yeaaah, I'm with {player_name}\non this one. I don't see jack.
Something IS there, though it makes\nitself one with the darkness. Perhaps\na fiend with some special adaptation?
See? Malinda knows what's up. All right,\nlet's go and get it to ix-nay on the uck-say.
I would ask a moment's forbearance,\nmy liege.
Unless we ascertain for certain whether\nit drains the blood of its prey, we'll not\ndisprove the villager's allegations.
Okay, so... What do we do?
I propose we attack after it strikes and we\nhave witnessed it drinking the blood of the\nlivestock or villager it falls upon.
What?! You would sit by and let it claim\nanother victim?!
That would produce the most concrete\nevidence. And if other villagers are present\nto witness it, so much the better.
Perhaps so, but that would mean allowing\nthe loss of a life we could have saved.\nI cannot agree to such a thing.
But if we act before securing proof and the\nvillagers persist in their suspicions, our\nintervention will have been pointless.
HEY! Do you two mind not fighting right\nnow? He's running away! We've got to go\nafter him!
How come I got saddled with this job?\nI could be asleep in bed, but noooo,\nI've got to patrol the village all night...
If we just locked up that weird brat who\nclaims to be a vampire, we'd be done with\nit and I could go saw all the logs I want.
Everybody here's been acting all scared\nof me because of you, you JERK!
ChiLD...? SucH A juiCY LitTLe mORseL...\nGivE Me yOUr bLoOOoOD!
Not happening, dummy. And you can\nhowl all you like—you're not scaring me!
Did you two slowpokes finally catch up?\nI already caught the thing.
True, it doesn't appear able to\nmove, but... What did you do?
For a trueblooded vampire like Vania,\nimmobilizing a lesser fiend like this\nwith her gaze alone is a simple matter.
I see. In any case, I'm relieved to see there\nwere no further casualties. Now we can—
This mean ol' fiend was the one who\nattacked your cows and stuff! I had\nnothing to do with it, see?
Now just you watch.\nI'll teach this jerk a lesson!
NwAAaAaaARGH...! The ThirST...\nMy bOdy...mY LiFE...! STeaLiNG mY...\nNO! PleAsE...!
The fiend is...shriveling up?\nWhat am I witnessing?
Vania has sucked out—rather,\n＂extracted＂ the fiend's life essence.
So this is a vampire's power...
Hee hee, did everybody see that?\nI took care of the bad guy for you all!
Wait, no, hold on!\nHey, you guys, tell them I'm not!
C'mon, you kids know I'm not—
But...why? I didn't...\nI didn't do anything wrong...
